    saf:"For 6 Div, Artillery and Army Intelligence the lesson is about the chain, not the shooter. Map every node in the sense-to-shooter chain that depends on an RF link and name the single point of failure if each is jammed. The near-term model that survives is layered: radar cue for area search, AI optical guidance for the terminal phase, and a guidance path that does not depend on the operator's RF link. No single chain should have one RF or optical point of failure \u2014 and target development must shorten to match how fast the adversary fields a counter. The Geran-4 appeared within weeks of the interceptor success being made public.",
