   div:{ d:"Add human-enabler targets as a standing category in target development, with their own collection and prioritisation logic.", o:"Div Comd / G2, on targeting-board advice.", a:"A target taxonomy split into material / command / human enabler; a standing ISR requirement for adversary training locations, throughput and graduation timing; supply-chain tracking of key components for capability forecasting.", t:"Develop and nominate human-enabler concentrations (training, maintenance, operator assembly) whenever the adversary is UAS-heavy.", x:"Collection against people and training cycles competes with material-target collection for scarce ISR.", m:"Were human-enabler nodes identified and actioned; did adversary operator quality or throughput drop?" },
