    saf:"Assess every MSR and engineer-constructed route against a drone-interdiction scenario: within ~200 km of a medium-range-drone adversary, it is targetable. A single bridge as the sole crossing is a single point of failure and the most targetable node \u2014 build in covered segments, dispersed supply nodes and pre-surveyed alternate crossings. Pre-position pontoon bridging and rapid-repair teams (materials staged, deployable within ~2 hours) before the primary bridge is struck. Design logistics nodes with the same deception as combat positions \u2014 dummy nodes, dispersed real nodes, covered approaches, irregular schedules \u2014 because the campaign worked against predictable, concentrated routes. Bridge interdiction by drone is now an engineer-adjacent offensive task to understand on both sides.",
